This paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms for policy evaluation, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on temporal-difference learning algorithms, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and convergence proofs, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
